description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you experienced in providing Complex Care to children and young people?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare is seeking experienced Health Care Assistants to support a young gentleman with complex care needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dedicated and compassionate Health Care Assistants who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user lives at home with his mum in Winsford. He is a happy, pleasant young gentleman who is fully dependent on his dedicated care team to support with his clinical and social needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When at home, he likes watching tv and films; he especially enjoys Teletubbies and Sport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He has limited communication however he uses gestures and some words to express his feelings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At times, our service user can become anxious and agitated when there are a lot of things going on; Therefore, we are looking for people with a calming nature who can comfort and reassure him when upset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He likes to go out into the community when able to and particularly likes going for car journeys.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to current circumstances, he is unable to attend school. However, once he does return to his educational setting you will be required to support throughout the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 6 months previous care experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Medication Administration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Personal Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Moving and Handling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Tracheostomy Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ventilation Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Peg Feeding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Learning Disability awareness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Epilepsy Awareness&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Days (12hour shifts)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Waking Nights (12hour shifts)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on his day to day life.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
